18/01/2009
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- Former Yugoslav National Army General Pavle Strugar, who was sentenced to seven and a half years in prison for involvement in military operations in Dubrovnik, Croatia, will be released on February 20th. 
The Hague war crimes tribunal announced on Friday (January 16th) that the decision was based on Strugar's poor health, his voluntarily surrender in October 2001 and his behaviour while behind bars. 
(RTS, Antena M, RTV, Hayat - 16/01/09)
